# 9. 思ってるって思いたい

Akito & Toya: ♪——!
Spectator A: BAD DOGS are totally lit again tonight! Are they seriously still in high school?!
Spectator B: Akito's sheer power draws you in while Toya is great at the technical stuff. He's got a mysterious quality as well. I doubt any of the young groups around here can compete!
Spectator A: What about Ken's daughter?
Spectator B: Oh, that's right! Man, what a great time to be alive!
Musician: Tsk. Doesn't anyone have anything better to talk about?
Akito: What's wrong with you? What are you getting all pissed off about?
Musician: Oh, it's nothing. I'm just sick of everyone around here talking about Ken's daughter all the time, is all.
Toya: Shiraishi's?
Musician: That reminds me. I hear you're both performing in an event soon. It must be annoying having to be compared to some girl riding her father's coattails.
Toya: No, that event is...
Akito: Actually, I'm looking forward to it. We're going to crush them with our singing.
Musician: Crush them?
Akito: Yeah, I'm going to show them what real talent is so they'll never make stupid jokes about surpassing RAD WEEKEND again.
Toya: .....
Musician: Seriously?! That's great! Ken's girl will look like a snot-nosed brat compared to you two!
Musician: In that case, maybe I'll lend you guys a little support of my own.
Toya: Support?
Akito: Hey, don't stick your nose where it doesn't belong. This is our problem to deal with.
Musician: Oh, don't worry about me. I won't do anything...too bad.
Toya: .....
Len: Here we are. I wonder where those two are right now. Hm?
Len: It's pitch black. And am I shaking? I wonder if the phone is in a bag or something.
Akito: Would you like the equipment moved over here?
New Staff: Yeah. Thanks for helping out, Akito, Toya.
Len: Akito and Toya were the names of the other two! It sounds like they're close by.
Len: They seem a bit busy today, though. Maybe I should try again some other time.
An: The big show is tomorrow! Are you ready, Kohane?
Kohane: Yeah. Thanks to you, I've been able to get a lot of practice singing in front of people. I-I think I'm ready!
An: I've explained how the event works and we've done everything we can, so let's give it our best tomorrow!
Kohane: Right. I'll do my best!
Kohane: I know I said I'd be fine, but I'm still really nervous... I wonder if there will be a lot of scary-looking people at this event...
Kohane: Huh? Isn't that that guy from before?
Toya: Oh. It was Azusawa, wasn't it?
Kohane: That's right. Um, your name was Aoyagi, right? Are you on your way to Weekend Garage?
Toya: No, I was on my way to the park nearby to practice. And I said it before, but there's no need to be so formal.
Kohane: Oh... R-Right... Um, is it just you today?
Toya: Yeah. This is something I do on my own.
Toya: My singing still isn't as good as Akito's when it comes to grabbing the attention of the crowd.
Kohane: I see...
Toya: Azusawa, can I ask you something?
Kohane: Huh? Oh, sure.
Toya: Are you really serious about holding an event that surpasses RAD WEEKEND?
Kohane: ...What?
Toya: Please tell me.
Kohane: I guess...I want to...be serious about it...
Kohane: Um, I only just recently learned about that event, so I'm sure you probably think I'm not very serious about it, but...
Toya: .....
Kohane: The first time I saw An singing, my heart started racing.
Kohane: And my heart was thumping even harder the first time we sang together. I remember thinking, I never knew something could be so fun!
Kohane: I've never really had a dream of my own like An, but now I feel like I want to sing with her and chase after her dream together.
Kohane: I still have a long way to go, but it makes me really happy to be able to work so hard toward something with her.
Toya: I see.
Kohane: Oh, and um... Thank you for inviting us to the event.
Toya: Hm?
Kohane: If you hadn't invited us, I think I probably would have been too scared to do something like this.
Kohane: So I'm going to give it my best tomorrow!
Toya: ...Right.
An: Kohane! Over here! Hey, you got some new clothes!
Kohane: I, um...didn't really know what I was looking for, so I had the staff help me pick it out. D-Do I look all right?
An: Hehe. I think it suits you just great. Oh, what if you tried wearing contacts next time?
Kohane: P-Putting something in my eyes like that is a little scary...but maybe I'll give it a try.
Akito: So you guys made it. If you want, you can use the green room in the back.
An: Gotcha. Thanks, Akito.
Kohane: U-Um, I-I'm looking forward to tonight!
Akito: Same here. I know you're probably nervous, this being your first time and all, but good luck.
An's Voice: Hehe. Kohane, you sound a bit nervous.
Kohane's Voice: W-Well, yeah... Just look at how many customers there are out front...
Akito: Look at 'em laughing like fools.
Akito: Let's go, Toya. It's time to crush them.
Toya: Akito, do you have a minute first?
Akito: Hm?
